meta {
  name: GET charging_statistics (v2.10.0)
  type: http
  seq: 39
}

get {
  url: {{charging_host_url}}/charging_statistics
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  v2.10.0 - Historical charging-session aggregator on the CARIAD
  charging-stats host.

  Different vhost than the other SEAT/CUPRA endpoints in this
  collection: this one lives on
  ``prod.emea.mobile.charging.cariad.digital`` rather than on
  ``ola.prod.code.seat.cloud.vwgroup.com``. Accepts the same Bearer
  access token from the SEAT/CUPRA IDK client.

  Endpoint reference: Timwun/Cupra-WeConnect-Bruno-Collection
  (Charging Statistics sequence), independently parsed in
  seat_cupra._get_from_charging_host + ``get_status`` v2.10.0.

  Response shape (observed across CUPRA Born + Leon e-Hybrid):
    {
      "totalEnergyChargedInKwh": 1234.5,
      "sessions": [
        {
          "startedAt": "2026-05-30T18:42:11Z",
          "energyChargedInKwh": 38.2,
          "durationInMinutes": 27,
          "currentType": "DC"
        },
        ...
      ]
    }

  Newer firmware wraps the list under data.sessions; both paths
  handled by the parser.

  Soft-fails to {} on 401 / 403 (older firmware that doesn't expose
  this host, accounts without the Connect subscription) and 404
  (vehicle has never recorded a session).
}
